==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stiletto
<hw>Sti*let"to</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Stilettos</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[It., dim. of
<ets>stilo</ets> a dagger, fr. L. <ets>stilus</ets> a pointed
instrument. See <er>Style</er> for writing, and cf.
<er>Stylet</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A kind of dagger with a
slender, rounded, and pointed blade.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A pointed instrument for making eyelet holes in
embroidery.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A beard trimmed into a pointed form.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The very quack of fashions, the very he that⟦br⟧
Wears a <qex>stiletto</qex> on his chin.</q>
<rj><qau>Ford.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stiletto</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Stiletto
<hw>Sti*let"to</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Stilettoed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Stilettoing</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <def>To stab or kill
with a stiletto.</def> <rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Still</ent>⟦br⟧
